# Auth RBAC - Go Backend

Production-ready authentication and role-based access control (RBAC) API built with Go, PostgreSQL, JWT, and Docker.

---

## Project Structure

```
.
├── cmd
│   └── main.go
├── config
├── docker-compose.yml
├── go.mod
├── go.sum
├── internal
│   ├── auth
│   │   └── handler.go
│   ├── middleware
│   │   ├── auth_middleware.go
│   │   └── role_middleware.go
│   └── server
│       └── server.go
```

---

## Features

* User Registration
* User Login
* JWT Authentication
* Role-Based Authorization
* PostgreSQL Integration
* Docker for local development

---

## Live API

Base URL:

```
https://auth-rbac.onrender.com
```

### Register User

```
POST https://auth-rbac.onrender.com/api/auth/register
```

Example:

```
curl -X POST https://auth-rbac.onrender.com/api/auth/register \
  -H "Content-Type: application/json" \
  -d '{
    "username": "testuser",
    "email": "test@example.com",
    "password": "123456",
    "role": "user"
  }'
```

### Login

```
POST https://auth-rbac.onrender.com/api/auth/login
```

---

## Environment Variables

```
DATABASE_URL
JWT_SECRET
```

---

## Run Locally

With Docker:

```
docker compose up -d
```

Run app:

```
go run ./cmd
```
